In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 7 through March 13, 2010, as Save Your Vision Week. The purpose of this week is to raise awareness about the importance of maintaining good vision and taking action to protect one's sight. The proclamation emphasizes the impact of vision loss on individuals of all ages and provides recommendations for maintaining good eye health, such as getting regular eye examinations, maintaining a healthy diet, not smoking, and wearing suitable eye protection. The article encourages Americans to visit the National Eye Institute website for eye care resources and information. The proclamation also mentions that the United States Congress has authorized and requested the President to proclaim the first week in March as Save Your Vision Week since 1963.